Granit Xhaka’s agent, José Noguera has disclosed that his client has reached an agreement to join Bundesliga side, Hertha Berlin. According to Noguera, Arsenal will now decide on a transfer fee with Hertha, before the Switzerland international will finally depart Emirates. “Look, I will say it frankly and honestly, we are in agreement with Hertha BSC and would like to go to Berlin,” Noguera told Blick. “We have told Arsenal’s club boss Raul Sanllehi and sporting director Edu Gaspar, as well as the new coach Mikel Arteta. “Arsenal was informed about all the steps, the player and Hertha are clear. It’s only about the transfer fee of the clubs.” Xhaka, who was stripped of Arsenal’s captaincy in November, featured in his side’s 1-1 draw with Bournemouth on Thursday Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.